<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="437" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1623,2009]" pageId="6" pageNumber="437">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1804,1829]" pageId="6" pageNumber="437">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is reference to the name of the region in the native language of the area where the 
<typeStatus box="[1388,1436,1805,1829]" pageId="6" pageNumber="437">type</typeStatus>
series was collected; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marathe &amp; Sanborn &amp; Kunte" authorityYear="2018" box="[387,494,1839,1864]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Rustia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kodagura">
<emphasis box="[387,494,1839,1864]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="437">kodagura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Kodava language means anything that belongs to the Kodagu (Coorg) region.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
