<taxonomicName authority="Marathe &amp; Sanborn &amp; Kunte, 2018" authorityName="Marathe &amp; Sanborn &amp; Kunte" authorityYear="2018" box="[1241,1409,1584,1606]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Rustia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="439" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kodagura" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1241,1409,1584,1606]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="439">Rustia kodagura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="8" pageNumber="439" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="439">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
Separate millimeter-scales are at the bottom of the type specimens and genitalia.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1717,2030]" pageId="8" pageNumber="439">
<emphasis box="[199,287,1717,1742]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="439">Thorax.</emphasis>
Prothorax olivaceous marked with piceous, female brownish where male olivaceous. 
<collectingRegion box="[1354,1436,1717,1742]" country="Sri Lanka" name="Central" pageId="8" pageNumber="439">Central</collectingRegion>
olivaceous fascia, mildly biconcave shaped piceous fasciae on either side, anterior ends broad and merging medially on posterior end. Paramedian and lateral fissures almost equal in length, piceous. Lateral ambient fissure, lateral angle of the pronotal collar and posterior pronotal collar margin piceous. Pronotal collar wider than anterior mesothorax, almost as wide as abdominal tergite 4. Mesothorax ochraceous and piceous dorsally, olivaceous laterally. 
<collectingRegion box="[263,345,1897,1922]" country="Sri Lanka" name="Central" pageId="8" pageNumber="439">Central</collectingRegion>
piceous fascia, narrow anteriorly expanding laterally near posterior to merge with scutal depressions, extending to cruciform elevation appearing trilobed at terminus. Piceous along parasidal suture. Piceous fascia along lateral lateral sigillae, narrowed anteriorly, expanding posteriorly terminating in wing groove. Cruciform elevation olivaceous. Ventral side olivaceous.
</paragraph>
